<paragraph id="7E039F1CC3059F48BF552EEA30AB1D1E" pageId="0" pageNumber="301">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6A3FD0983737845868173F5B023FDF74" pageId="0" pageNumber="301">
<taxonomicName id="9021CD418E1547770C1DE7FDE31842C3" authorityName="Dognin" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Pero" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pero atridisca" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atridisca">
<emphasis id="F02B5D3D438D666BAA92F6E5E5D21C29" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="301">Pero atridisca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from Angasmarca, La Libertad Department, Peru. The discovery of this species in Arequipa expands its range south in the Andes more than 1000 km (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0F5A75CCFFE245EA5E747A33B16B8E44" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Geographic distribution of Pero lopezi Vargas &amp; Palacios, sp. nov. (white stars) and Pero atridisca Dognin, 1906 (squares) in Peru. Symbols: black square (locality type), white square (new record)." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.43.54177.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/460412" pageId="0" pageNumber="301">4</figureCitation>
). Adult and male genitalia were illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="44548AE207063B1EBAB7C8C3D0C6DD4C" author="Poole, RW" journalOrPublisher="Department of Agriculture" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="1 - 257" refId="B15" refString="Poole, RW, 1987. A taxonomic review of the new world moth genus Pero (Lepidoptera: Geometridae). Technical Bulletin of the U. S. Department of Agriculture 1698: 1 - 257" title="A taxonomic review of the new world moth genus Pero (Lepidoptera: Geometridae). Technical Bulletin of the U. S." volume="1698" year="1987">Poole (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. The species identity awaits further study and confirmation by molecular data (DNA barcoding).
</paragraph>
